/* The maximum length of a transaction name. The Berkeley DB backend generates transaction names from a sequence expressed as a base 36 number with a maximum of MAX_KEY_SIZE (currently 200) bytes. The FSFS backend generates transaction names of the form <rev>-<base 36-number> where the base 36 number is a sequence value with a maximum length of MAX_KEY_SIZE bytes. The maximum length is 212, but use 220 just to have some extra space: 10 -> 32 bit revision number 1 -> '-' 200 -> 200 digit base 36 number 1 -> '\0' */ #define SVN_FS__TXN_MAX_LEN 220
